      {
        "id": 269425,
        "name": "",
        "username": "barnett",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/ac91a4/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-06-07T19:14:07.429Z",
        "cooked": "<p>When the screen lock feature is enabled in privacy settings and Signal is unlocked, a notification is created with a “Lock Signal” button.</p>\n<p>If you dismiss this notification, or disable the notification channel in Android settings, there is no way to lock Signal again besides force stop or rebooting. Android previously allowed apps to make notifications like this persistent, but that’s no longer possible.</p>\n<p>To avoid this problem and make sure the user can always manually lock Signal, when screen lock is enabled there should be a “Lock Signal” button in the menu. Alternatively, Signal could automatically lock when the notification is dismissed, like Firefox Focus.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2025-06-07T19:14:07.429Z",
